[
    {
        "text": "As part of our series",
        "start": 0.008,
        "duration": 1.674
    },
    {
        "text": "on relaxation and placement,",
        "start": 1.683,
        "duration": 1.825
    },
    {
        "text": "this video talks about the soft palate.",
        "start": 3.509,
        "duration": 3.11
    },
    {
        "text": " ",
        "start": 6.62,
        "duration": 6.655
    },
    {
        "text": "An overall nasal sound can be caused",
        "start": 13.276,
        "duration": 2.462
    },
    {
        "text": "either by tension in the throat,",
        "start": 15.739,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": "or by a lowered soft palate.",
        "start": 17.39,
        "duration": 2.284
    },
    {
        "text": "When the soft palate is lowered,",
        "start": 19.675,
        "duration": 1.782
    },
    {
        "text": "it allows some air to come through here,",
        "start": 21.458,
        "duration": 2.634
    },
    {
        "text": "into the nasal cavity.",
        "start": 24.093,
        "duration": 1.825
    },
    {
        "text": "That makes the voice live",
        "start": 25.919,
        "duration": 1.258
    },
    {
        "text": "more in the face than in the body.",
        "start": 27.178,
        "duration": 2.141
    },
    {
        "text": "Luckily there is a very easy way",
        "start": 29.32,
        "duration": 1.626
    },
    {
        "text": "to tell if this is a problem for you.",
        "start": 30.947,
        "duration": 1.998
    },
    {
        "text": "If you put your fingers",
        "start": 32.946,
        "duration": 1.008
    },
    {
        "text": "on the bridge of your nose,",
        "start": 33.955,
        "duration": 1.317
    },
    {
        "text": "you will feel it vibrate",
        "start": 35.273,
        "duration": 1.213
    },
    {
        "text": "if your soft palate is lowered.",
        "start": 36.487,
        "duration": 1.929
    },
    {
        "text": "Try it.",
        "start": 38.417,
        "duration": 0.902
    },
    {
        "text": "Put your fingers here and say NN-AH.",
        "start": 39.32,
        "duration": 6.552
    },
    {
        "text": "I feel a vibration for the N,",
        "start": 45.873,
        "duration": 1.758
    },
    {
        "text": "which has a lowered soft palate,",
        "start": 47.632,
        "duration": 1.777
    },
    {
        "text": "but not for the AH,",
        "start": 49.41,
        "duration": 1.285
    },
    {
        "text": "which has a raised soft palate.",
        "start": 50.696,
        "duration": 2.554
    },
    {
        "text": "There are only three sounds",
        "start": 53.259,
        "duration": 1.319
    },
    {
        "text": "in English that are nasal,",
        "start": 54.579,
        "duration": 1.205
    },
    {
        "text": "with a lowered soft palate.",
        "start": 55.785,
        "duration": 1.785
    },
    {
        "text": "They are N, M, and NG.",
        "start": 57.571,
        "duration": 3.078
    },
    {
        "text": "Many other languages have nasal vowels,",
        "start": 60.65,
        "duration": 2.264
    },
    {
        "text": "where the soft palate is down,",
        "start": 62.915,
        "duration": 1.785
    },
    {
        "text": "including Mandarin, Polish,",
        "start": 64.701,
        "duration": 2.395
    },
    {
        "text": "Hindi, French, and Portuguese.",
        "start": 67.097,
        "duration": 3.102
    },
    {
        "text": "If your native language has nasal vowels,",
        "start": 70.2,
        "duration": 2.396
    },
    {
        "text": "you'll really want to pay attention to this.",
        "start": 72.597,
        "duration": 3.16
    },
    {
        "text": "First, test yourself. Let's take the word ON.",
        "start": 75.758,
        "duration": 3.769
    },
    {
        "text": "It has the AH",
        "start": 79.528,
        "duration": 0.991
    },
    {
        "text": "as in FATHER vowel and the N consonant.",
        "start": 80.52,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "Say it slowly, holding your nose.  ON.",
        "start": 83.081,
        "duration": 6.872
    },
    {
        "text": "Were you able to make the vowel",
        "start": 89.954,
        "duration": 1.396
    },
    {
        "text": "with no vibration?",
        "start": 91.351,
        "duration": 2.038
    },
    {
        "text": "Another word, SONG,",
        "start": 93.39,
        "duration": 1.817
    },
    {
        "text": "has the AW as in LAW vowel",
        "start": 95.215,
        "duration": 2.126
    },
    {
        "text": "followed by the NG consonant, song.",
        "start": 97.342,
        "duration": 7.306
    },
    {
        "text": "Were you able to make the vowel",
        "start": 104.649,
        "duration": 1.364
    },
    {
        "text": "with no vibration?",
        "start": 106.014,
        "duration": 1.928
    },
    {
        "text": "A lot of my students get concerned with the",
        "start": 107.943,
        "duration": 2.028
    },
    {
        "text": "idea of raising and lowering the soft palate.",
        "start": 109.972,
        "duration": 2.721
    },
    {
        "text": "It's sort of hard to feel, and hard see.",
        "start": 112.709,
        "duration": 3.039
    },
    {
        "text": "So I've told them",
        "start": 115.749,
        "duration": 1.207
    },
    {
        "text": "just to focus on keeping it lifted.",
        "start": 116.957,
        "duration": 2.246
    },
    {
        "text": "Somehow this does not interfere",
        "start": 119.204,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "with the nasal consonants.",
        "start": 120.905,
        "duration": 1.61
    },
    {
        "text": "I've never had a student",
        "start": 122.516,
        "duration": 1.222
    },
    {
        "text": "fix their overall sound",
        "start": 123.739,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "by keeping the soft palate raised,",
        "start": 125.27,
        "duration": 1.936
    },
    {
        "text": "but then mess up their nasal consonants.",
        "start": 127.207,
        "duration": 2.015
    },
    {
        "text": "So just focus on keeping it lifted.",
        "start": 129.223,
        "duration": 3.162
    },
    {
        "text": "How do you lift it.",
        "start": 132.386,
        "duration": 1.325
    },
    {
        "text": "There are a few ways",
        "start": 133.712,
        "duration": 1.031
    },
    {
        "text": "to get used to the feeling and the idea.",
        "start": 134.744,
        "duration": 2.395
    },
    {
        "text": "One way to get used to feeling",
        "start": 137.156,
        "duration": 1.547
    },
    {
        "text": "your soft palate is to suck through a straw.",
        "start": 138.704,
        "duration": 2.713
    },
    {
        "text": "When you suck through a straw,",
        "start": 141.418,
        "duration": 1.34
    },
    {
        "text": "your soft palate automatically closes",
        "start": 142.759,
        "duration": 2.571
    },
    {
        "text": "to prevent the liquid",
        "start": 145.331,
        "duration": 0.897
    },
    {
        "text": "from going up into your nasal cavity.",
        "start": 146.229,
        "duration": 2.267
    },
    {
        "text": "So, see if you can feel it close.",
        "start": 148.505,
        "duration": 5.547
    },
    {
        "text": "And if you can't then try sucking up",
        "start": 154.053,
        "duration": 1.906
    },
    {
        "text": "through the straw and holding it there.",
        "start": 155.96,
        "duration": 2.3
    },
    {
        "text": "If you hold it, that might make",
        "start": 158.261,
        "duration": 1.269
    },
    {
        "text": "you more aware of the feeling here,",
        "start": 159.531,
        "duration": 1.745
    },
    {
        "text": "especially when you let go.",
        "start": 161.277,
        "duration": 1.603
    },
    {
        "text": "See if you feel anything release.",
        "start": 162.881,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "So go ahead, open a can of soda,",
        "start": 164.642,
        "duration": 1.986
    },
    {
        "text": "treat yourself to that,",
        "start": 166.629,
        "duration": 1.316
    },
    {
        "text": "and practice feeling your soft palate.",
        "start": 167.946,
        "duration": 6.483
    },
    {
        "text": "Another method that may help you",
        "start": 174.43,
        "duration": 1.626
    },
    {
        "text": "lift your soft palate is to just think",
        "start": 176.057,
        "duration": 2.102
    },
    {
        "text": "of creating more space back here.",
        "start": 178.16,
        "duration": 1.975
    },
    {
        "text": "If you're creating more space,",
        "start": 180.136,
        "duration": 1.277
    },
    {
        "text": "you may automatically",
        "start": 181.414,
        "duration": 1.094
    },
    {
        "text": "lift your soft palate to accommodate that.",
        "start": 182.509,
        "duration": 2.38
    },
    {
        "text": "So you can focus on creating space in",
        "start": 184.897,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "the back of your mouth or throat as you talk.",
        "start": 186.698,
        "duration": 2.525
    },
    {
        "text": "Another way to feel your soft palate",
        "start": 189.224,
        "duration": 2.321
    },
    {
        "text": "is to watch yourself raising and lowering it.",
        "start": 191.546,
        "duration": 2.824
    },
    {
        "text": "Switch back and forth between AH and NG.",
        "start": 194.371,
        "duration": 3.418
    },
    {
        "text": "When you make the NG, of course,",
        "start": 197.79,
        "duration": 1.618
    },
    {
        "text": "you're lowering your palate.",
        "start": 199.409,
        "duration": 1.999
    },
    {
        "text": "So switch back and forth between the two,",
        "start": 201.409,
        "duration": 2.26
    },
    {
        "text": "and try to keep your tongue",
        "start": 203.67,
        "duration": 1.023
    },
    {
        "text": "in the same position.",
        "start": 204.694,
        "duration": 1.412
    },
    {
        "text": "That means it's your",
        "start": 206.107,
        "duration": 0.776
    },
    {
        "text": "soft palate that has to move.",
        "start": 206.898,
        "duration": 2.192
    },
    {
        "text": "Watch yourself in a mirror.",
        "start": 209.091,
        "duration": 1.702
    },
    {
        "text": "I'll demonstrate now,",
        "start": 210.794,
        "duration": 1.158
    },
    {
        "text": "so you should see what that looks like.",
        "start": 211.953,
        "duration": 9.84
    },
    {
        "text": "So, the soft palate:",
        "start": 221.794,
        "duration": 1.856
    },
    {
        "text": "it's hard to see and hard to feel,",
        "start": 223.651,
        "duration": 2.198
    },
    {
        "text": "but it does play an important role in the",
        "start": 225.85,
        "duration": 2.043
    },
    {
        "text": "placement of the voice in American English.",
        "start": 227.894,
        "duration": 2.878
    },
    {
        "text": "Play around with these exercises,",
        "start": 230.773,
        "duration": 1.979
    },
    {
        "text": "especially the last one,",
        "start": 232.753,
        "duration": 1.624
    },
    {
        "text": "and see if you can get used to the idea",
        "start": 234.378,
        "duration": 2.064
    },
    {
        "text": "of keeping your soft palate raised",
        "start": 236.443,
        "duration": 2.095
    },
    {
        "text": "in all vowel sounds and",
        "start": 238.539,
        "duration": 1.618
    },
    {
        "text": "most consonant sounds in American English.",
        "start": 240.158,
        "duration": 3.324
    },
    {
        "text": "This video is part of a series",
        "start": 243.483,
        "duration": 1.746
    },
    {
        "text": "on relaxation and placement.",
        "start": 245.23,
        "duration": 1.879
    },
    {
        "text": "If you liked the video,",
        "start": 247.11,
        "duration": 1.157
    },
    {
        "text": "check out the previous one",
        "start": 248.268,
        "duration": 1.31
    },
    {
        "text": "on the relaxation of the throat.",
        "start": 249.579,
        "duration": 2.406
    },
    {
        "text": "Please put any questions you have",
        "start": 251.986,
        "duration": 1.666
    },
    {
        "text": "in the comments section.",
        "start": 253.653,
        "duration": 1.745
    },
    {
        "text": "That's it, and thanks so much for using",
        "start": 255.399,
        "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
        "text": "Rachel's English.",
        "start": 258.16,
        "duration": 1.301
    }
]